raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Manages and responsible for success of assigned programs.  Leads and directs staff, manages financial and budgetary activities of the program.  Demonstrates knowledge of the principles, methods and practices associated with the field.

raw_data.title: Behavioral Analyst
raw_data.description: Conducts observations in operational settings to analyze people and implements plans to improve behavior.  Reviews policies and procedures related to behavioral health.

raw_data.title: Data Analyst
raw_data.description: Conducts analysis of data to improve operations or execute a business’s strategy.  Develops software or procedures to systematically collect, identify, organize, and report on data.

raw_data.title: Database Analyst
raw_data.description: Organizes and makes sense of collections of information to create functional database systems.  Evaluates, designs, reviews, modifies, and implements databases.  Creates, modifies, and maintains reporting tools and scripts for databases.
raw_data.required_certifications_or_licenses: Professional certification in applicable database technology, e.g. SQL, DBA

raw_data.title: SME
raw_data.description: Provides expert level advice to agencies to improve business or financial performance.  Utilizes technical knowledge and experience at the highest level to analyze, plan, design, and implement programs and policies.

raw_data.title: Emergency Management Specialist
raw_data.description: Coordinates emergency management operations and disaster response activities.  Assists with policy and procedure development related to preparedness, emergency operations, and management of disasters such as hurricanes, floods, fires, infectious disease outbreaks, or man-made technological events.

raw_data.title: Health Communication Specialist
raw_data.description: Draft health education messages and products for a variety of health promotion efforts.  Coordinate with education providers, health care providers, and other public service providers.  Develop or coordinate graphics and writing products.   Draft or review drafts of evaluation plans to ensure projects meet the principles of sound health communication evaluation.

raw_data.title: Public Health Analyst I
raw_data.description: Analyzes public health data to provide reports, presentations, or scientific literature.  Organizes data using database tools and/or statistical programs.  Performs studies of medical and research literature to develop public health messaging or documentation.

raw_data.title: Public Health Analyst II
raw_data.description: Analyzes public health data to provide reports, presentations, or scientific literature.  Organizes data using database tools and/or statistical programs.  Performs studies of medical and research literature to develop public health messaging or documentation.  Provides more varied and complex tasks than a Level I Public Health Analyst.

raw_data.title: Application Programmer III
raw_data.description: Works independently to solve problems and develop programs for complex and difficult applications.  Writes software code to develop applications based on requirements and specifications.  Directs work of lower level programmer team members to assign lower level tasks.  Updates, maintains, repairs, and creates software applications of large and complex scale. Proficiency on both front end and database (Back-end) sides of programming.  Develops architecture documentation.  Provides system assessments.

raw_data.title: Senior Statistician
raw_data.description: Utilizes complex and advanced statistics and computer systems/software such as SAS, SPSS, and PL/SQL to generate reports and analysis.  Generates documentation and reports for business and technical consumers of data.

raw_data.title: Financial Manager
raw_data.description: Maintains overall responsibility for financial, audit, and grant management programs.  Conducts and oversees financial audits and project financial reviews.   Contributes as a subject matter expert on financial tasks or initiatives.  Assesses compliance of financial management systems.  Assists agencies with accountability for use of grant funds.

raw_data.title: Project Coordinator
raw_data.description: Arranges schedules and regulates workflow within business units and smaller teams to accomplish project deliverables within scope, schedule and budget.  Tracks schedules, develops project progress reports, and works directly under the supervision of a program manager or higher-level staff member.

raw_data.title: Clinical Geneticist
raw_data.description: Works in a clinical setting to diagnose and manage families with hereditary disorders.   Works to identify causes in birth defects, developmental delays, autism, epilepsy, and others.  Collects, analyzes, and reports on medical data.  Develops scientific literature for publications.

raw_data.title: Data Entry Clerk
raw_data.description: Performs entry and validation of data into a computer system. Performs administrative tasks such as data collection, archival, and correspondence.

raw_data.title: Scheduler
raw_data.description: Conducts phone calls with medical clinics and hospitals to schedule visits for medical record abstraction.  Schedules and assigns Medical Record Abstractors to sites to perform abstraction.

raw_data.title: Medical Record Abstrator
raw_data.description: Visits hospitals, health care related clinics, and offices.  Reviews medical records and completes abstraction forms per standard operating procedures.  Abstracts relevant medical, socio-demographic, and diagnostic information.  Regularly documents and reports the number of abstractions performed, challenges, and suggestions for improvements.

raw_data.title: Task Manager
raw_data.description: Leads management and consulting service projects that include planning, analysis, and execution.  Coordinates complex and/or technical resources to ensure task completion within the schedule and budget.   Has demonstrated experience leading teams of highly diverse and/or technical personnel

raw_data.title: Health Marketing Specialist
raw_data.description: Develops promotional materials such as newsletters, emails, templates, graphics, social media, and website content for health promotion activities.  Collaborates with health educators and medical professionals to collect and identify health data that will be used to help improve health and evaluate effectiveness and outcomes.

raw_data.title: Senior Strategy Practitioner
raw_data.description: Serves as a Program Manager or Subject Matter Specialist on projects related to an area of relevant management consulting such as enterprise risk management, (including competitive sourcing support), program/portfolio management, financial strategy and operations including public/private partnerships, assurance services, financial management, tax matters, or a related field.

raw_data.title: Health IT Systems Engineer - Intermediate
raw_data.description: Applies experience and domain knowledge in supporting government, state, and/or commercial health IT initiatives related but not limited to Electronic Health Record, health data sharing and interoperability, health exchange networks, and health benefits claims systems. Performs systems engineering design, integration and implementation. Defines, analyzes, and documents requirements and specifications. Develops procedures to automate or improve existing systems. Manage and maintain systems and infrastructure throughout the product life cycle. Assists with design of software architecture and data flow. Performs integration, test, and debug. Develops appropriate required system documentation.

raw_data.title: Health IT Systems Engineer - Senior
raw_data.description: Applies experience and domain knowledge in supporting government, state, and/or commercial health IT initiatives related but not limited to Electronic Health Record, health data sharing and interoperability, health exchange networks, and health benefits claims systems. Performs systems engineering design, integration and implementation. Defines, analyzes, and documents requirements and specifications. Develops procedures to automate or improve existing systems. Manage and maintain systems and infrastructure throughout the product life cycle. Assists with design of software architecture and data flow. Performs integration, test, and debug. Develops appropriate required system documentation.

raw_data.title: Financial Analyst
raw_data.description: Performs financial studies and analysis for assigned projects.   Generates financial reports and cost models.  Assists with development and management of budgets.  Performs financial audits.  Collects and stores pertinent financial data according to program policies.

raw_data.title: Health IT Software Engineer - Senior
raw_data.description: Applies experience and domain knowledge in supporting government, state, and/or commercial health IT initiatives related but not limited to Electronic Health Record, health data sharing and interoperability, health exchange networks, and health benefits claims systems. Designs, modifies, develops, writes, tests, and releases software applications and resources. Develops performance requirements and specifications. Develops software documentation such as flowcharts, system interface diagrams, UML diagrams, unit tests, and training. Assists with project planning and tracking, configuration management and quality assurance.

raw_data.title: Health IT System Administrator - Senior
raw_data.description: Provide systems management by administering various servers and functions (including web, file, application, backup, pre-production, and production). Troubleshoots network performance issues and creates and maintains a disaster recovery plan. Works with data/systems that are health-centric, related to symptoms, effects, and spread of infectious diseases. Optimizes system operation and resource utilization, and perform system capacity analysis and planning. These systems are supporting government, state, and/or commercial health IT initiatives related but not limited to Electronic Health Record, health data sharing and interoperability, health exchange networks, and health benefits claims systems.

raw_data.title: Health IT Cybersecurity Analyst - Intermediate
raw_data.description: Analyzes and defines security requirement for computer systems and networks. Works with data/systems that are health-centric, related to symptoms, effects, and spread of infectious diseases. Performs risk analyses of computer systems and applications including health exchange networks, and health benefits claims systems during all phases of the system development life cycle. Prepares Assessment & Authorization (A&A), Authority to Operate (ATO) and the Authority to Connect (ATC) request package or similar work products as required. Provides such services to the Centers for Disease Control or other federal or state agencies tasked with public health system maintenance.

raw_data.title: Health IT Database Administrator - Senior
raw_data.description: Analyzes and defines security requirement for computer systems and networks. Works with data/systems that are health-centric, related to symptoms, effects, and spread of infectious diseases. Performs risk analyses of health IT systems and specialized applications including health data sharing and interoperability, health exchange networks, and health benefits claims systems during all phases of the system development life cycle. Prepares Assessment & Authorization (A&A), Authority to Operate (ATO) and the Authority to Connect (ATC) request package or similar work products as required.

labor_categories.labor_category: Health IT Quality Assurance Specialist - Intermediate

raw_data.title: Health IT Quality Assurance Specialist - Intermediate
raw_data.description: Implements Quality Assurance Policy and Procedures throughout the product lifecycle supporting government, state, and/or commercial health IT. Works with data/systems that are health-centric, related to symptoms, effects, and spread of infectious diseases. Conduct QA surveillance and reviews to ensure quality of products. Escalate quality issues to appropriate levels of management. Collect and analyze quality metrics and provide input to management and design reviews. Conduct Audits and Training related to the Quality System. Provide quality monitoring and management of subcontractor quality for IT Health systems for the CDC and other organizations involved in managing and implementing IT Health systems.

raw_data.title: Health IT Database Analyst - Intermediate
raw_data.description: Designs, implements and maintains databases and data collection systems supporting government, state, and/or commercial health IT to maximize statistical efficiency and quality. Works with data/systems that are healthcentric, related to symptoms, effects, and spread of infectious diseases. Develop analysis and reporting capabilities related to projects focused on infectious disease data collection. Identify and interpret data trends. Look for process improvement opportunities. Maintain database documentation. Provides such services to the Centers for Disease Control or other federal or state agencies tasked with public health system maintenance.

raw_data.title: Health IT Enterprise Infrastructure Architect
raw_data.description: Strategically designs and implements information technology systems and networked software architectures that support core business functions, and assure high availability for health related programs. Works extensively with database management systems, such as REDCap, to input, categorize, and analyze health data. Provide assistance and support services in evaluating systems engineering solutions for integration, installation, and testing and life-cycle support of new and upgraded systems associated with delivery of infrastructure capabilities supporting government, state, and/or commercial health IT. Evaluate and recommend changes to current and future network requirements to reconcile the needs of a variety of user groups and recommend best industry practices to improve efficiency and quality. Provides such services to the Centers for Disease Control or other federal or state agencies tasked with public health system maintenance.

raw_data.title: Health IT Clinical Systems Consultant
